summary: TIRE FAILURE ON WESCO BOAT TRAILER TIRE.  TIRE LABELED " TRAIL AMERICA" AND HAS MARKINGS "DOT AAKC"  AND APPEARS TO BE MANUFACTURER ON 06/04.  NOTE TRAILER MANUFACTURER  IS "WESCO", A MFG NOT AVAILABLE ON YOUR COMPLAINT FORM SO I PICKED ANOTHER JUST AS PLACE FILLER.  ALSO THE TIRE BRAND, TRAIL AMERICA, IS NOT LISTED ON YOUR CHOICES EITHER. *TR

DT*: THE CONTACT OWNS A TRITON TRAILER, MODEL NUMBER L2512.  WHILE PULLING THE EMPTY TRAILER; IT BLEW OVER ONTO ITS SIDE INTO THE PASSENGER LANE.  THE TRAILER BROKE FREE OF THE TOWING BALL AND SLID DOWN THE FREEWAY AND STRUCK THE BACK OF THE TRUCK, CAUSING DAMAGE.  THIS HAS BEEN REPORTED TO THE INSURANCE COMPANY.  THE OWNERS' MANUAL DOES NOT ADDRESS THE SAFETY HAZARDS OF A NO TOW OR  UNDER LOADING.  THE DEALERSHIP WAS NOTIFIED.  *AK
